# API Response Format

## Standard Format
```json
// Success
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {...},
  "message": "Description",
  "timestamp": "ISO8601"
}

// Error
{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Description",
  "error_code": "CODE",
  "timestamp": "ISO8601"
}
```

## Required Fields
- `status`: success | error | pending
- `message`: Human-readable description
- `data`: Response data (success only)
- `error_code`: Machine code (error only)
- `timestamp`: ISO 8601

## Implementation
```python
def create_response(status: str, data: dict = None, message: str = ""):
    response = {
        "status": status,
        "message": message,
        "timestamp": datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + "Z"
    }
    if data:
        response["data"] = data
    return response
```
